    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_111492070" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/111492070" />
    <a title="Quinn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2310262-quinn"><img alt="Quinn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1300839213p2/2310262.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/111492070?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Quinn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Quinn" href="/user/show/2310262-quinn">Quinn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780451224187" href="/book/show/2988016-comanche-moon">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2310262-quinn?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2310262-quinn?shelf=library-book">library-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2310262-quinn?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2310262-quinn?shelf=5-stars">5-stars</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer111492070" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer872449690886852619"><i>Comanche Moon</i> is the kind of epic love story that they just don&apos;t write any more. Of course, as my friend Lady Jayne pointed out, they apparently didn&apos;t write them even when this book was published. I cannot imagine what editors were thinking when they asked author Catherine Anderson to change her story if she wanted to sell it, but we should be very grateful that she didn&apos;t listen.<br/><br/>Most romance readers, like me, will have heard of Comanche Moon even if they haven&apos;t read it. It is a classic for a</span>
  <span id="freeText872449690886852619" style="display:none"><i>Comanche Moon</i> is the kind of epic love story that they just don't write any more. Of course, as my friend Lady Jayne pointed out, they apparently didn't write them even when this book was published. I cannot imagine what editors were thinking when they asked author Catherine Anderson to change her story if she wanted to sell it, but we should be very grateful that she didn't listen.<br /><br />Most romance readers, like me, will have heard of Comanche Moon even if they haven't read it. It is a classic for a reason - it's good. Very good. Interestingly, I wouldn't necessarily have categorised this as a romance per se. "Epic Love Story" seems to be a much more accurate description. Whatever you want to call it, reading it's an experience worth having.<br /><br />Catherine Anderson brings her story to life, portraying with gritty realism the journey of being a white woman ripped away from everything she knows and held captive at the complete mercy of the savage Comanches. There are not endless pages of dull, descriptive narrative, but the setting and characters are vividly rendered with great skill.<br /><br />One of the many strengths of this novel is that the author remained true to the setting and the characters. This was a harsh landscape populated with harsh people (both the whites and the Native Americans) where violence was common place. Nothing is prettied up for the reader, and that makes for a very gripping, immersive, emotional experience.<br /><br />Another strength is the characters. Not just Loretta and Hunter, who in particular is complex and captivating, but also the cast of secondary characters, each of whom were fully realised and added immeasurably to the story.<br /><br />I don't know why I waited so long to read this one, but if you've left it languishing on your TBR like I did, it's time to dig it out and go on this adventure. You wont be sorry you did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="872449690886852619" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


